Instructions for Board Work Session- July 28, 2020; 6:00 p.m.

The board work session will be live streamed via Facebook. If you would like to make a public comment you need to follow these instructions:
1. You must complete the following form: https://forms.gle/jkGaSFKp9Egz3gaf9
2. You must log in to the meeting on the following link, and not on the live Facebook feed. https://lcsd2.zoom.us/j/96449426292
3. When you log in to the Zoom meeting you will need to use your given name (no aliases) and be prepared to use live video when it is your turn to make a comment. The time for each comment will be limited by the board chair dependent on the number of people that have signed up. You will be notified when it is your turn to speak.

The schedule for the meeting will go as follows:
1. 6:00 p.m.- Call to Order
2. 6:00 p.m.- 6:30 p.m.- Presentation of Plan
3. 6:30 p.m.- 6:45 p.m.- Board Question and Answer Session
4. 6:45 p.m.- 7:15 p.m.- Public Comments
5. 7:15 p.m.- Summary and Debrief
6. 7:30 p.m.- Work Session Ends

post_text:
Cokeville High School Graduation/Diploma Ceremony
May 27, 2020, 6:00 p.m.

Cokeville High School Football Field – Parking Pass Required

To help our graduates have one last time with their classmates, a diploma ceremony with their parents will be held. This will help meet the Covid19 guidelines expected and approved by our health department. Only cars with parking passes will have access to the field. Please help us in providing a safe environment and ceremony. Thank you.

We hope to have the live event broadcasted both on the Bear Lake Radio (KVSI) and streamed online through SVI media. The senior slide show, graduation speaker(virtually), and valedictorian and salutatorian speeches(virtually) will also be added to the archived Graduation/Diploma Ceremony. Our goal is to have the live and virtual events merged and available by 8:00 p.m. on SVI media.

post_text:
PLEASE READ CAREFULLY!!

Lincoln County School District #2 will be offering Summer Grab-n-Go Meals the month of June for children 18 years of age and younger. Pick up will be on Monday's and Thursday's only from 11:00 a.m.-12:00 p.m. at Cokeville High School, Star Valley High School and Thayne Elementary. Each pick-up day there will be two days' worth of meals- two breakfasts and two lunches. Responses must be submitted by 9:00 a.m. the day of pick-up and we appreciate those that are submitted well in advance. You only need to specify how many children you are picking up for, not how many meals you need. BOTH breakfast and lunch are provided at the same time. Please specify the location you will be picking the meals up from. Meal requests can be made at the following link: https://forms.gle/bb3v4v4iuGGtzh5r8.

post_text:
What a wonderful time for us to be able to share with you the Mission Statement for Lincoln County School District #2.

The Mission Statement for Lincoln County School District #2 is “Success at the Next Level”. This statement is at the core of decisions that are made district-wide. We put student’s success first.

We envision success at the next level being accomplished by cultivating relationships through respectful, considerate, sincere and honest interactions; by accepting learning at high levels as the main purpose of our school district; by working collaboratively to achieve our collective purpose, and by determining our effectiveness on the basis of results rather than intentions.

post_text: Today at 3:00 p.m. Governor Gordon will hold a press conference. You may watch this live on wyomingpbs.org. We anticipate receiving further guidance regarding the school closure that is in effect until April 30. Based on the information received from that press conference, the Board of Trustees will hold a special board meeting Friday, April 24 at 5:00 p.m. A ZOOM link will be posted on our Facebook page as well as our website. It is anticipated that the public session of that meeting will begin at approximately 5:10 p.m. Information will be sent to parents and staff following that meeting with a plan for the rest of the 2019-2020 school year.

post_text:
Today Governor Gordon announced that Wyoming schools are to remain closed until April 17th. LCSD#2 Board of Trustees and Administration support this recommendation. Superintendent of Public Instruction Balow stated that ”school doors may be closed to students, but Wyoming education is open for business”. “The desire by teachers to connect with their students and provide learning opportunities has been inspiring. Teaching and learning while practicing social distancing is a new concept for many. Teachers, parents, and students all need support in order for it to be successful."

Each district must have an Adaptive Education Plan in place by April 6 in order to continue to receive state funding. LCSD#2 administration will present our plan at a board meeting Wednesday, April 1.

post_text: LCSD#2 administrators and teachers are preparing a long term plan that will enable students to continue with their learning should the COVID-19 closure extend beyond April 3. Each member of our school district is essential in supporting each other and our students in this journey. We know that education is a service, not a place. If we have to shift from the brick and mortar of our schools to remote based learning opportunities, our job remains to provide quality instruction to our students in a safe and welcoming way. We hope this closure will be over as soon as possible. Our administrators, teachers and staff miss having traditional contact with our students.

post_text: Lincoln County School District #2 school closure! Late this afternoon, Sunday, March 15, Governor Mark Gordon and State Superintendent Jillian Balow recommended that all schools are closed to students through at least April 3. LCSD#2 is following the recommendation of Governor Gordon and Supt. Balow and will close all schools until April 6. LCSD#2 Administration will release further plans after meetings are concluded Monday morning. Updates will be on our websites, social media and SVI. District administrators will be contacting staff over the next few hours.
text: Lincoln County School District #2 school closure! Late this afternoon, Sunday, March 15, Governor Mark Gordon and State Superintendent Jillian Balow recommended that all schools are closed to students through at least April 3. LCSD#2 is following the recommendation of Governor Gordon and Supt. Balow and will close all schools until April 6. LCSD#2 Administration will release further plans after meetings are concluded Monday morning. Updates will be on our websites, social media and SVI. District administrators will be contacting staff over the next few hours.

post_text: As of right now school will continue in LCSD#2 as planned. Supt. Erickson has a conference call scheduled at 8:30 a.m. on Monday morning with Governor Gordon, Jillian Balow and Dr. Alexia Harrist. Following the call the district administration team will meet to discuss recommendations based on that conference call. We encourage parents to do what they feel is best for their own family. Leniency with absences will be handled on a case by case basis. Updates will be provided on social media and school websites as they become available. If more urgent communication is needed the school district will use the emergency school notification system. A message will be sent out later this afternoon to all households containing the same information as this post.

post_text:
Every year Lincoln County School District #2 conducts a Preschool Census. The information gathered helps us plan for future programming needs, as well as to provide us with the contact information needed to reach out to next year's incoming kindergarten students.

If you have a child who is 0-5 years old and currently not enrolled in kindergarten, we'd appreciate you taking the time to fill out the online survey. If you choose to not complete the online census, there will be a census worker in your area who will gather this information during January. This survey only needs to be filled out once per school year.

The following link will take you to the census:
https://bit.ly/2XHwMJU

We appreciate you taking the time to assist us with our census this year!

For questions please contact Nathan Wescott- 307-885-7143 or Emily Isaacson- 307- 885-7129.

Thank you!

post_text: Minor bus accident this morning on Hwy 89 in the Grover area with Route Bus #7. All students are safe. Administrators are on-site to supervise the process.

We have traditionally recognized veterans every year in LCSD2. This year, we are adding a luncheon and revising the school program schedule.

VETERAN’S DAY SCHEDULE-Monday, November 11, 2019

For veterans in the upper valley, they are invited to attend the following programs:
Afton Elementary at 9 a.m.
Osmond Elementary at 10 a.m.
Star Valley Middle School at 11 a.m.
LUNCH at the LCSD2 District Office at 11:45 a.m. (RSVP to Amanda McAdams at 885-7130 by November 4)
Star Valley High School at 1 p.m.

For veterans in the lower valley, they are invited to attend the following programs:
Etna Elementary at 9 a.m.
Thayne Elementary at 10 a.m.
Star Valley Middle School at 11 a.m.
LUNCH at the LCSD2 District Office at 11:45 a.m. (RSVP to Amanda McAdams at 885-7130 by November 4)
Star Valley High School at 1 p.m.

Veterans- PLEASE RSVP to Amanda McAdams at 307-885-7130 by November 4 if you would like to attend the luncheon.

Cokeville will continue with the tradition they have used in previous years.

Every year Lincoln County School District #2 conducts a Preschool Census. The information gathered helps us plan for future programming needs, as well as to provide us with the contact information needed to reach out to next year's incoming kindergarten students.

If you have a child who is 5 years old and currently not enrolled in school, or younger, we'd appreciate you taking the time to fill out the online survey. If you choose to not complete the online census, there will be a census worker in your area who will gather this information during January. This survey only needs to be filled out once per year.

The following link will take you to the census:
https://goo.gl/forms/wb6h2CDzC6XlLXMy1

We appreciate you taking the time to assist us with our census this year!

For questions please contact Nathan Wescott- 307-885-7143 or Emily Isaacson- 307- 885-7129.

Thank you!

post_text: In a special board meeting last night, the school board voted to interview Amanda McAdams, Layne Parmenter and Matt Erickson for the position of School Superintendent of Lincoln County School District #2. The interviews will take place on Tuesday, February 27, beginning at 4:15 PM. The Board has formed a committee of parents, business owners, and school employees to provide input about each candidate through the interview process. There will be an open forum for the public at 7:00 PM at the District Office where each candidate will answer a few questions that were generated by the public. If the public has a question they would like answered in this forum, they can submit the question to Amanda Welch. awelch@lcsd2.org. The school board will select a few questions to be asked from those submitted.
text: In a special board meeting last night, the school board voted to interview Amanda McAdams, Layne Parmenter and Matt Erickson for the position of School Superintendent of Lincoln County School District #2. The interviews will take place on Tuesday, February 27, beginning at 4:15 PM. The Board has formed a committee of parents, business owners, and school employees to provide input about each candidate through the interview process. There will be an open forum for the public at 7:00 PM at the District Office where each candidate will answer a few questions that were generated by the public. If the public has a question they would like answered in this forum, they can submit the question to Amanda Welch. awelch@lcsd2.org. The school board will select a few questions to be asked from those submitted.

post_text: If you are interested in submitting a question for the board to consider as part of the public forum in conjunction with the interviews for superintendent please email your question to awelch@lcsd2.org by February 25 at 4:00 p.m. From the questions submitted, four or five will be selected to ask.

post_text: At Board Meeting held on February 8, the Board announced that at this time they would be opening the position for Superintendent to in-district applicants only. Applications will be accepted until February 20. The Board will, in an executive session, interview selected candidates on February 27. It is anticipated they will make the announcement of the new superintendent at Board Meeting scheduled for Tuesday, March 6.

post_text:
This morning, there was an accident north of Etna involving a LCSD#2 school bus and a passenger vehicle. Local emergency personnel responded to the accident. Students who were being transported on the school bus were evaluated by district staff. Students were then transported to their school. Parents of those students were notified throughout the process.

LCSD#2 is grateful to all First Responders and staff/volunteers who helped with this situation. Thank you.
